dataElements.name: TB patients (new and relapse) with HIV test result recorded
dataElements.description: TB patients (new and relapse) notified during the year and had an HIV test result recorded in the TB register during the same year. This should include TB patients who were known to be HIV-positive before being diagnosed with TB, as well as TB patients with a negative HIV result from previous testing that was acceptable to the clinician (e.g. done in the last 3-6 months in a reliable laboratory).
